The Debian Package aptupdatechecker
===================================

A basic application that:

- Checks for software and firmware updates in the background.
- Notifies the user when updates are available.

Usage
-----

To start the service, run::

  sudo systemctl start aptupdatechecker

To stop the service, run::

  sudo systemctl stop aptupdatechecker

To start the service on system boot, run::

  sudo systemctl enable aptupdatechecker

To prevent the service from starting on system boot, run::

  sudo systemctl disable aptupdatechecker

